    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Ok, so this is my first deck report but I&#39;m trying to make no beginner-errors.<br>
Bid high from 5-8 depending on your feeling if you might be facing a burden punishing deck, normally 6.<br>
Anybody who bids 5 or 6 and loses the coin toss will be relying on sam (if not playing hobbits) so if he sees he will not get the Inn from you he must change his starting fellowship or face a lot of burdens at the beginning.<br>
Get the gaffer from you deck, remove 4 burdens. If you get sting or Gandalf+ glamdring, use it first before you play too much. If you haven&#39;t just play all your fellowship cards. 5 drawing possibilities for a Gandalf should be enough that you should draw him latest on site 3, so you can use his events. With 5 possibilities on a Gondor comapnion there is also a good chance to play your Brands.<br>
Everything is quite selfexplantory, everybody except gandalf and maybe aragorn is expendable in this deck. You need Aragorn or Boromir as your main fighter against Nazgul with their flaming sticks.<br>
Save your Servants for fights which are important to win. Try to double move if the situation allows, leaving your opponent behind.<br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
Well more or less standard Uruk-hai beatdown, with 3 Spies and site 7, pretty good archery protection.<br>
The troops and lurtz are your stoppers so try to have at least one at each site, Uruk captains brings them back if need to be.<br>
The Raiding Parties survive also a lost skirmish.<br>
Enque punishes 6 companions or high bidders.<br>
Tower assasin gets rid of a pesky ally or two.<br>
Sarumans Power helps against those Last alliances and Promises.<br>
<br>
So I hope you have phun with this deck. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23511"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23511" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
